# The amendment reaction (see the amendment-flow decision in PROJECT.md and AGENTS.md).
#
# Modou's constitution is the law. Changing the law — or the living specs that
# project it — is an *amendment* and requires steward review, so an agent cannot
# silently weaken a boundary to make CI pass. The review requirement is the
# reaction: a merge cannot relax the law without a human accepting it.
#
# What "the law" actually is here matters: the protected file must be the boundary
# whose edit turns CI green after drift, not a showcase of it.
#   - tests/self_governance.rs is Modou's SELF-GOVERNING constitution — the boundaries
#     Modou enforces on itself (serde_json-only, engine must-not-import runner). It is
#     the file an agent would have to weaken to make Modou's own CI pass, so it is the
#     primary thing to protect.
#   - deny.toml is the supply-chain gate backing the same dependency-light invariant
#     (license allowlist, advisories); weakening it likewise relaxes the law.
#   - src/constitution.rs is only the bundled DEMO constitution (target `example-core`)
#     the published binary and fixtures use — protected so the adoption showcase cannot
#     rot, but it gates nothing on its own.
#
# This file designates the steward for the protected paths. Designation alone only
# auto-requests review; to make review *required* (block a merge that relaxes the
# law), the repository admin must enable branch protection on the default branch
# with "Require review from Code Owners". Until that setting is on, this file
# documents intent and requests review but does not block.

/crates/modou/tests/self_governance.rs   @tacticaldoll
/crates/modou/src/constitution.rs        @tacticaldoll
/deny.toml                               @tacticaldoll
/openspec/specs/                         @tacticaldoll
